      "extra": {
        "message": "Sensitive User Data (pwd_hash) Passed to Template Context\n\nThe User.get method retrieves the full user record including `pwd_hash` and `is_admin` fields. Since the auth_user_processor likely passes the full User object to templates via context, the password hash crosses a trust boundary into the template rendering context. With autoescape=False, this data could be exposed.\n\nImpact: Password hashes could be exposed in rendered HTML or error pages, enabling offline password cracking attacks.\n\nFix: Exclude sensitive fields like `pwd_hash` from queries used to populate template contexts, or create a separate method that returns only non-sensitive user fields.",
        "severity": "HIGH",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-200"
          ],
          "finding_id": "72d92243-b083-4624-8523-4f7371bab439"
        }
