    {
      "check_id": "CWE-209",
      "path": "sqli/middlewares.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 61,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 61,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Error Handler Passes Exception Object to Template\n\nThe error handlers `handle_40x` and `handle_50x` pass the full exception object to Jinja2 templates via `{'error': exc}`. With autoescape=False, if templates render exception details (e.g., `{{ error }}` or `{{ error.text }}`), internal application details could be exposed.\n\nImpact: Internal error details, stack traces, or application internals could be exposed to end users through error pages.\n\nFix: Pass only safe, user-friendly error messages to templates instead of full exception objects.",
        "severity": "MEDIUM",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-209"
          ],
          "finding_id": "d027f857-033b-4c3c-b7ce-67bb59794052"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-312",
      "path": "sqli/schema/config.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 12,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 12,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Redis Connection Without Authentication\n\nThe Redis configuration schema defines only `host`, `port`, and `db` fields but has no `password` field. This means Redis is connected to without authentication, which is insecure if the Redis instance is accessible on the network.\n\nImpact: An attacker with network access to the Redis instance can read/write session data, potentially hijacking user sessions or injecting malicious data.\n\nFix: Add a `password` field to the Redis configuration schema and pass it to the `aioredis.create_pool()` call.",
        "severity": "MEDIUM",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-312"
          ],
          "finding_id": "613fe3e5-1b8b-44fd-a474-71b4ef02bb09"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "check_id": "CWE-319",
      "path": "sqli/services/db.py",
      "start": {
        "line": 15,
        "col": 1
      },
      "end": {
        "line": 15,
        "col": 100
      },
      "extra": {
        "message": "Database Connection Without TLS/SSL\n\nThe PostgreSQL connection DSN does not include any SSL/TLS parameters (e.g., `sslmode=require`). Database credentials and all query data are transmitted in cleartext over the network.\n\nImpact: An attacker performing network sniffing can intercept database credentials and all data transmitted between the application and database, including PII.\n\nFix: Add `sslmode=require` or `sslmode=verify-full` to the DSN string to enforce encrypted connections.",
        "severity": "MEDIUM",
        "metadata": {
          "cwe": [
            "CWE-319"
          ],
          "finding_id": "a594996c-8818-4490-894d-7f43cb0425aa"
        }
      }
    },
